{"name": "haystack-redis", "metadata": {"name": "haystack-redis", "version": "0.0.1", "classifiers": ["Environment :: Web Environment", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Topic :: Internet :: WWW/HTTP :: Dynamic Content", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules"], "home_page": "https://github.com/steinbro/haystack-redis", "license": "BSD", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["django-haystack", "redis", "whoosh"], "summary": "Use redis as a persistence layer for Whoosh and Haystack", "upload_time": 1621464173}, "documentation": ["# haystack-redis\n\nA Whoosh storage engine using redis for persistence. A Haystack\n`SearchBackend` subclass is also provided. Normally the `STORAGE` key could\njust be set but Haystack 2.0.0alpha is only aware of `file` and `ram`\nbackends.\n\nThis is especially useful for small sites hosted on Heroku, which does not allow\nwriting to local disk. The `REDISTOGO_URL` environment variable is read,\nfalling back to the localhost default port.\n\n## Usage\n\nConfigure your Haystack connections in `settings.py`:\n\n```\nimport tempfile\nHAYSTACK_CONNECTIONS = {\n    'default': {\n        'ENGINE': 'haystack_redis.RedisEngine',\n        'PATH': tempfile.gettempdir(),\n    },\n}\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "haystack_redis", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "haystack_redis.RedisSearchBackend", "bases": ["WhooshSearchBackend"], "methods": [{"name": "haystack_redis.RedisSearchBackend.setup", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Defers loading until needed."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "haystack_redis.RedisEngine", "bases": ["WhooshEngine"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "haystack_redis.Redis